    • move

      public abstract boolean move​(java.awt.Point direction)
      Abstract method to be implemented by its children to check if the one GameObject can move to a certain given direction, if so, move the object.
      Parameters:
      direction - A Point object specifying the direction vector the GameObject to be moved to.
      Returns:
      If the GameObject can move, the method move the GameObject and true value is returned; Otherwise, false is returned.
      See Also:
      Player.move(Point), Crate.move(Point)
